al: bonus/split/buyback/merger; Low = routine: dividend/AGM).","why_useful":"Rising promoter & institutional ownership and clean corporate actions are confirming signals; falling promoter stake or pledging is a governance/skin-in-the-game warning.","why_it_can_fail":"Shareholding is a lagged quarterly snapshot; promoter % can fall for benign reasons (QIP, ESOP dilution). Pledge & insider detail are deferred (placeholders below)."},"snapshot":{"dimensions":{"Market":{"verdict":"neutral","score":1,"drivers":["+ Trades above its 200-day average (+4%).","+ 50-day average above the 200-day (golden cross).","+ Within 10% of its 52-week high.","\u2212 Lagging the NIFTY 500 by -4pp over 12 months.","\u2212 In a deep drawdown (-33% from its peak)."],"rule":"Points: +1 price above its 200-day average \u00b7 +1 a golden cross (50-day \u2265 200-day) \u00b7 +1 within 10% of the 52-week high \u00b7 +1 beating the NIFTY 500 over 12 months; \u22121 for each opposite, and \u22121 if more than 25% below its peak. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less, otherwise neutral."},"Business":{"verdict":"neutral","score":1,"drivers":["\u00b7 Average quality (60/100).","+ 2.18\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","\u00b7 Moderate leverage (D/E 0.72\u00d7, interest cover 2.7\u00d7).","\u00b7 Profit up 47% YoY \u2014 modest."],"rule":"Points across the four business flags: +1 for each that is 'good' (quality, cash conversion, balance-sheet safety, earnings momentum), \u22121 for each that is 'weak'. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less."},"Valuation":{"verdict":"positive","score":2,"drivers":["+ P/E at the 14-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."],"rule":"Cheap \u2014 P/E below the 30th percentile of its own 10-year range \u2014 scores +2 (supportive); expensive (above the 70th) scores \u22122; mid-range is 0. A peak/cyclical-earnings flag discounts a cheap read to +1. NOTE: 'positive